                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2381: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-30T14:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 30, 1919, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your telegrams August 21, 7 p.m. and August 23, 1 p.m.</p>
                <p>The Department desires to receive the text of the understanding reached by the
                    several interested powers and by them communicated to the Chinese Government in
                    regard to the withholding of financial assistance.</p>
                <p>It wishes furthermore to be informed of the purpose of the provisions for
                    supervision of expenditures of the loans referred to, also of such other facts
                    as may enable it to judge of their relation to the understanding mentioned and
                    to the pending proposals for the consortium.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
